I added unit tests. To do this, I grabed a copy of Unity from http://throwtheswitch.org/. To add tests, I had to refactor the code a bit. I created geo_functions.c which holds the core logic that interfaces with libmaxminddb. Now the vmod_geo.c code only has the core varnish internals and makes calls to functions in geo_functions.c which makes it easier to write functional tests.

Altered the code to have a .h file for function declarations. Updated configure and makefile to support telling the vmod where the data file is instead of hard coding it in the c code. Updated the code to only open the database file on the init function to drastically improve performance.
